The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Pak move to control chucking
Karachi: The Pakistan Cricket Board (PCB) has launched a campaign to spot bowlers with illegal deliveries early in their careers to avoid embarrassment at the international level, the PCB chairman wrote in a letter on Sunday. I am writing to seek your assistance in checking the increasing instances of illegal bowling action in Pakistan cricket at all level, Shaharyar Khan said in a letter to the countrys leading umpires. Pakistan pacers Shoaib Akhtar and Shabbir Ahmed have come under theICCs scrutiny for their bowling styles. Akhtar has had the legality of his delivery questioned three times but was cleared. because of a deformity on his bowling arm. (AFP)  Copyright 
